   <body>
      <section>
         <ol>
            <li>On the Machine Server, log off the obop account (using the sequence Start-&gt;Shutdown-&gt;Log Off).</li>
            <li>Log onto the Machine Server using the obsetup account (password: SetupServer).</li>
            <li>Start the Backup Configuration Utility (Start -&gt; Machine Server Applications -&gt;
               Backup Configuration Utility), as shown in Figure <xref href="#r209FDAE-BB02-11F0-8723-09173F13E4C5/fig_mc1_rkz_qzb">1</xref>. <fig id="fig_mc1_rkz_qzb">
                  <title>Figure 1: Accessing the Backup Configuration Utility</title>
                  <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                         placement="break"
                         id="image_nc1_rkz_qzb"
                         align="center"/>
               </fig>
            </li>
            <li>Use the drop-down box labeled Backup Server to confirm that the desired server has been
               added to the list of backup servers (see Figure <xref href="#r209FDAE-BB02-11F0-8723-09173F13E4C5/fig_hvv_skz_qzb">2</xref>). If it has, skip to step <xref href="#r209FDAE-BB02-11F0-8723-09173F13E4C5/li_ehj_vkz_qzb">6</xref>.</li>
            <li>Add the backup server.  (Note, if desired, the Tab key can be used to toggle through the necessary fields)<ol>
                  <li>Enter a Server Name in the box provided.</li>
                  <li>Enter the four IP Address Segments in the next box.</li>
                  <li>Click the <uicontrol>Add Server</uicontrol> button to add the server.</li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li id="li_ehj_vkz_qzb">Select the desired backup server from the Backup Server
               drop-down.</li>
            <li>Click the <uicontrol>Apply</uicontrol> button to apply the changes.</li>
            <li>Click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button to close the backup configuration
               utility.</li>
            <li>Log off the obsetup account.</li>
            <li>Follow the directions in SOP-16-010 (Manual MDMS Backup) to manually trigger a server
               backup. <fig id="fig_hvv_skz_qzb">
                  <title>Figure 2: Checking Currently Configured Backup Servers</title>
                  <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                         placement="break"
                         id="image_jvv_skz_qzb"
                         align="center"/>
               </fig>
            </li>
         </ol>
